rComments: Nicole is AMAZING!! she made research methods enjoyable and interesting! assignments are manageable and Nicole makes everything really easy to understand and relate to real life! definitely take this class with her!!

highly recom.taking her class. Very excited about the subject. she never sounds boring at all. very energetic teacher that makes the class engaged in learning. need to keep up with readings and do comp questions she assigns. daily quizes straight from the comp questions can used inclass. lab alot of work. know studyguide concepts youll be ready !!

This class is by default really boring but she made class very enjoyable. If you make flashcards from her lecture slides and from the book, you?ll ace the midterm and final. Just pay attention in lecture, read, and put a good effort into your lab assignments/research paper and you?ll get an A.

Boring subject, but she's great! Her lectures are easy to follow, organized, and she makes research methods seem so much more interesting than it actually is. It's easy to get an A if you do your labs and follow her review sheets. It's not necessary to do the readings if you go to class. Nicole Wilson, thank you for making this class not suck!
Nicole Wilson was great for Children's Thinking. She tells you exactly what is important on her powerpoints and as long as you use the study guides she provides you should do fine.

Children's thinking was really interesting and Nicole did a really good job teaching material that may seem dry to some. 2 blue book tests, gives test questions out before hand and picks 6 out of 16 questions to be on the test. I studied hard but learned a lot. You really know your stuff by the end of the quarter

Nice teacher and happy to chat during office hours but her grading policy is pretty weird, where you only get an A/B on a paper if you do exactly as she says, following an exact format in a robotic way. Think of it as a math formula. Forget what you learned in previous English classes. No content needed to do well, just write exactly how she wants.

Nicole's a great teacher.  She's easy to talk to and helps you when you need it.  Core class was TOO MUCH WORK, and she grades pretty rough.  During the end of the quarter she gave a bit more check +'s.  Overall, cool gal!

Nicole is fun, but when I had her it was only her first time teaching the core class. Core class just SUCKS, overall, but you have to grin and bare it. I think once she losens up a bit she'll be a really good teacher. She's always really amped to help, dont write like she does = your screwed!

well first off, core class sucks, but she is not lenient when it comes to the syllabus. she's all about organization when it comes to papers. she likes a really weird structure that you have to follow, else she won't pass you. nice person, not so great teacher - may be because of the subject matter.
